  "text": "Head and stimulus orientation during conditioning procedure. The spring-loaded flexible coupling that attached the head to the restrainer was positioned at an angle of 12°in the posteroanterior direction. This angle aligned the horizontal semicircular canals so that they were orthogonal to the direction of gravity (0°pitch angle) [CITATION_1] . This angle approximately corresponds to the natural head angle maintained by rabbits [CITATION_2] . During optokinetic stimulation, the head-body of the rabbit was positioned at different pitch angles with respect to earth vertical. The plane of rotation of the optokinetic drum could also be independently aligned with respect to earth vertical. Four rabbits were conditioned with the head pitched 0°and the drum rotating in the horizontal plane (head pitch of 0°, OK S of 0°). Three rabbits received optokinetic stimulation with the drum pitched either 20°upward [counterclockwise (CCW)] or 20°downward [clockwise (C W)] and the head maintained at 0°pitch angle (head pitch of 0°, OK S of Ϯ20°). Three rabbits were stimulated with the head pitched 20°C C W or 20°C W and the drum at 0°(head pitch of Ϯ20°, OK S of 0°). Three rabbits were stimulated with the head pitched up 35°(CC W) and the drum also pitched up at 35°(head pitch of ϩ35°, OK S of ϩ35°).",
